In this article, President Trump discusses the issue of human trafficking and emphasizes that his administration will focus on ending this practice. He acknowledges that human trafficking is a dire problem both domestically and internationally, and recognizes the role of the internet in facilitating this modern phenomenon. The President pledges to direct various federal agencies, including the Department of Justice and Department of Homeland Security, to devote more resources to combating human trafficking. He expresses gratitude to those who have been working on this issue and emphasizes the need to raise awareness about the severity of the problem. The President concludes by stating that efforts will be made to prevent the horrific crimes associated with human trafficking.